(15, 1, '2016-01-30 23:13:51', '2016-01-30 23:13:51', '<h1>Freeform PDX</h1>\r\nWouldn''t it be great to have a fun radio station in Portland that plays a variety of great music morning, noon and night with no commercials? In 2015, three companies own over 75% of Portland''s radio dial. We want you to join our team of media rebels. Help us further liberate local airwaves from commercial control. Just like you can''t have too many local coffee shops or startup restaurants, you can not have too many local commercial-free radio stations.', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '13-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-30 23:13:51', '2016-01-30 23:13:51', '', 13, 'http://beta.freeformportland.org/2016/01/30/13-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(16, 1, '2016-01-30 23:14:18', '2016-01-30 23:14:18', '<h3>How can I donate? Are donations tax deductible?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Donations are 501(c)3 tax-deductible. Get a limted edition shirt through our indiegogo: http://bit.ly/1Hvk1qA</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Why does Portland need another listener-supported radio station?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>3 companies own 75% of our local airwaves. We feel that we have to do something about that. We are working in cooperation with every non-commercial radio station in Portland. Seriously. It''s a team effort. The only way to make radio better in Portland is to keep making better radio in Portland.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>What''s the Frequency, Kenneth? Projected launch date? Where''s the studio?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>With your help we will test FM broadcasting in 2015 and launch in 2016. Please sign up for the email list on this page.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Can I have a show? Will you play my band''s album please?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>More info soon! Please sign up for the email list on this page</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Volunteer opportunities? How can I help?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>email volunteer@freeformportland.org and tell us about yourself.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Will there be commercials? I''ll be able to hear this station from my house /car?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Freeform Portland is a non-profit commercial-free radio station coming to Low-Power FM in Portland in 2016. We''re using the same engineering team that created KZME and XRAY and working alongside every non-commercial radio station in Portland. We''re stoked to get to broadcasting ASAP and we need your help.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'FAQ', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'faq', '', '', '2016-02-11 22:42:12', '2016-02-11 22:42:12', '', 13, 'http://beta.freeformportland.org/?page_id=16', 0, 'page', '', 0),
